Pitso Mosimane's side notched up their fourth win in six league matches and though they are seven points behind leaders Bidvest Wits, they have four games in hand.Premier Soccer League sides may be grateful Sundowns have bigger fish to fry at next month's Club World Cup in Japan. Three of their scheduled December fixtures have been postponed.Highlands Park tried to take advantage of Sundowns' eagerness to attack but could not get past Denis Onyango.